The paper proposes a novel online modeling and classification scheme for streaming time series data. This involves developing a new technique called derivative delay embedding (DDE) and a non-parametric Markov geographic model (MGM). The paper focuses on machine learning and data analysis techniques for time series data, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed technique could be applied to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications, which further supports these sub-categories as likely choices.
